<subSubSection pageId="383" pageNumber="384" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="383.[151,1437,1430,1926]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">
This worldwide family, proposed by Macquart in 1835, contains nearly 700 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." box="[1107,1374,1467,1493]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Until recently these flies were treated within the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Soos" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[671,761,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Otitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Otitidae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Soos, A." box="[778,912,1503,1529]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" refId="ref374029" refString="Soos, A. (1984 c) Family Otitidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 9. Micropezidae - Agromyzidae. Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 45 - 59." type="book" year="1984">Soós 1984c</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Belcari, A. &amp; Girolami, V. &amp; Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F." box="[925,1153,1502,1529]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref345502" refString="Belcari, A., Girolami, V., Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F. (1995 b) Diptera Tephritoidea. In: Minelli, A., Ruffo, S. &amp; La Posta, S. (Eds.), Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. 72. Calderini, Bologna, pp. 1 - 13." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Belcari 
<emphasis box="[1014,1071,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">et al.</emphasis>
1995b
</bibRefCitation>
), but the use of the older name of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[249,353,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ulidiidae</taxonomicName>
is the correct one (
<bibRefCitation author="Kameneva, E. P. &amp; Korneyev, V. A." box="[566,899,1539,1565]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="65 - 72" refId="ref355121" refString="Kameneva, E. P. &amp; Korneyev, V. A. (1994) Holarctic genus Pseudoseioptera Stackelberg (Diptera: Ulidiidae (= Otitidae )). Part I. Phylogenetic relationships and taxonomic position. Journal of the Ukrainian Entomological Society, 1 (2) [1993], 65 - 72." type="journal article" year="1994">Kameneva &amp; Korneyev 1994</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T. &amp; Blagoderov, V. &amp; Mostovski, M. B." box="[910,1092,1539,1565]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="222 - 229" refId="ref362939" refString="Pape, T., Blagoderov, V. &amp; Mostovski, M. B. (2011) Order Diptera Linne, 1758. In: Zhang, Z. Q. (Ed.), Animal biodiversity: an outline of higher-level classification and survey of taxonomic richness. Zootaxa, 3148, 222 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3148.1.42" type="journal article" year="2011">
Pape 
<emphasis box="[972,1021,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[1103,1270,1539,1565]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
). In his “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Stirps Ortalidinae</emphasis>
”, rather than in the family 
<taxonomicName authority=", Rondani (1856" authorityName=", Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[586,874,1574,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Ulidiidae, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[704,874,1574,1601]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani (1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[886,956,1574,1601]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="5 - 37" refId="ref369927" refString="Rondani, C. (1869 a) Ortalidinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterologiae italicae prodromi. Pars VII. Fasc. 3 Linea A. Ortaloidi. Dipt. Stirps XX. Ortalidinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 1 (1), 5 - 37." type="journal article" year="1869">1869a</bibRefCitation>
) described 13 Palaearctic nominal species, eight considered as valid, four as junior synonyms and one as doubtful (
<bibRefCitation author="Soos, A." box="[949,1082,1611,1637]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" refId="ref374029" refString="Soos, A. (1984 c) Family Otitidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 9. Micropezidae - Agromyzidae. Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 45 - 59." type="book" year="1984">Soós 1984c</bibRefCitation>
, Rivosecchi 1992, 
<bibRefCitation author="Belcari, A. &amp; Girolami, V. &amp; Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F." pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref345502" refString="Belcari, A., Girolami, V., Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F. (1995 b) Diptera Tephritoidea. In: Minelli, A., Ruffo, S. &amp; La Posta, S. (Eds.), Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. 72. Calderini, Bologna, pp. 1 - 13." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Belcari 
<emphasis box="[1381,1437,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">et al.</emphasis>
1995b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kameneva, E. P." box="[236,424,1647,1673]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="19 - 46" refId="ref354969" refString="Kameneva, E. P. (1997) Revision of the Palaearctic species of Melieria R. - D. (Diptera, Ulidiidae, Otitinae). 1. The groups of species assigned to Hypochra Loew. Vestnik Zoologii, 30 (6) [1996], 19 - 46." type="journal article" year="1997">Kameneva 1997</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[444,634,1646,1673]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="5 - 37" refId="ref369927" refString="Rondani, C. (1869 a) Ortalidinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterologiae italicae prodromi. Pars VII. Fasc. 3 Linea A. Ortaloidi. Dipt. Stirps XX. Ortalidinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 1 (1), 5 - 37." type="journal article" year="1869">Rondani (1869a)</bibRefCitation>
proposed a new replacement names for a species previously described and named by Macquart. In his paper on the Rondani types at 
<collectionCode box="[838,922,1683,1709]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xa0v-1feb" name="Museo di Zoologia" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">MZUB</collectionCode>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Morge, G." box="[933,1100,1682,1709]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="909 - 945" refId="ref360243" refString="Morge, G. (1959 a) Monographie der palaearktischen Lonchaeidae (Diptera). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 9 (1 - 2), 1 - 92, 323 - 371, 909 - 945." type="journal article" year="1959">Morge (1959a)</bibRefCitation>
listed two unpublished names (
<emphasis box="[161,307,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">
nomina 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maibach et al." authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[251,307,1719,1745]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nuda">nuda</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) of Rondani. 
<bibRefCitation author="Soos, A." box="[460,601,1719,1745]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="133 - 137" refId="ref373811" refString="Soos, A. (1982 a) Wiederbeschreibung zweier Rondanischen Otitiden-Arten (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 28 (1 - 2), 133 - 137." type="journal article" year="1982">Soós (1982a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Soos, A." box="[611,668,1719,1745]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" pagination="253 - 260" refId="ref373879" refString="Soos, A. (1983) Untersuchungen des Typenmaterials der Rondanischen Sammlung. 2. Otitidae (Diptera). Acta Zoologica Academiae Scientiarum Hungaricae, 29 (1 - 3), 253 - 260." type="journal article" year="1983">1983</bibRefCitation>
) examined the type material in the 
<collectionCode box="[1059,1137,1719,1745]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mvk4-k796" name="Museo Zoologico La Specola, Universita di Firenze" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">MZUF</collectionCode>
and designated a 
<typeStatus box="[1334,1437,1719,1745]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">lectotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[192,553,1754,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Herina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ghilianii">
<emphasis box="[192,375,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Herina ghilianii</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[566,964,1754,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Ortalis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis box="[566,786,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Ortalis immaculata</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[977,1377,1754,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Ceroxys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pomariana">
<emphasis box="[977,1199,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Ceroxys pomariana</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Macheirocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Macheirocera grandis</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[554,919,1790,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Melieria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis box="[554,741,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Melieria etrusca</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[931,1328,1790,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Melieria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parmensis">
<emphasis box="[931,1150,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Melieria parmensis</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Melieria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subapennina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Melieria subapennina</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[526,923,1826,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Ulidiidae" genus="Tetanops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="383" pageNumber="384" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contarinii">
<emphasis box="[526,745,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">Tetanops contarinii</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
. Except for the type material of two nominal species, which are presumed lost, the type material has been recovered for all nominal species and is distributed between the 
<collectionCode box="[293,371,1899,1925]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mvk4-k796" name="Museo Zoologico La Specola, Universita di Firenze" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">MZUF</collectionCode>
(eight), 
<collectionCode box="[466,545,1899,1925]" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">MRSN</collectionCode>
(four) and 
<collectionCode box="[672,753,1899,1925]" country="France" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/4jmm-iazx" name="Musee Guimet d'Histoire Naturelle de Lyon" pageId="383" pageNumber="384">MHNL</collectionCode>
(one).
</paragraph>
